From next Monday, officials are to visit farmsteads countrywide embarking on a census of commercial farms. JOHANNESBURG – Statistics South Africa is to help with the country’s land reform process. From next Monday, officials are to visit farmsteads countrywide embarking on a census of commercial farms. The process seeks to determine the size of farms and what's being grown. It's hoped that this will help potential investors make informed decisions if they're looking at ploughing money into agriculture. Project director, Itani Magwaba, explains: “Individuals can use this information to make decisions about their own farming investments, on where and when they’ll invest.” WATCH: Agri SA maintains position on land after ANC meeting 